Why am I posting this now instead of last night when I was @nycballet? Here’s the story…

last night after the nutcracker my phone slipped out of my (very shallow) vintage coat pocket and back into the cab we took, and the cab flew off with my phone. i chased it a little before starting to panic. 

but the miracle was we used curb, so using my friends phone we were able to get in touch with the cab driver. he said to wait an hour and he’d come back. so in a corner bar in the pouring rain with christmas decorations we waited. and suddenly he called that he was nearby. 

the human in his cab had come along for the ride despite where they were going to come all the way uptown to get me my phone. and they just tapped the glass and waved. as i stood there in the pouring rain with my phone back.

the moral of the story is you should always use curb so if you loose something in a cab you can get it back. and i have a really good entire plot for a new york christmas rom com litterally ready to go, (there’s more) for whoever is ready to buy it. and also, i love new york.

Fourth, you will laugh.

🌸🌼 FLOWERS JOY WORKOUT! CELEBRATING A FULL MONTH OF MOVING MY BODY! 🌼🌸

If you’ve been following my stories you know I have posted every day of January, getting out, moving, jogging, walking, whatever worked. Today I celebrated a full month by having a joy workout- I danced to FLOWERS on repeat, wore fun clothes, had a snack and stayed hydrated. Dancing for an hour with my weights had me sweating harder than a lot of other days this month I’ll tell ya!! 

I won’t lie, there was a small unhealed part of me that went into this hoping in a month I’d look different. Loose a little weight, cause I’ve been conditioned to know that’s what made me beautiful and cast-able. But you know what I came out with instead? More energy than I’ve had the last couple years, slightly less anxiety, more smiles, feeling more in my body and happy with it on the inside than in a looong time. 

I also am willing (after arguing with my brain) to call it a win & a success even though I took days off. I even took a day off that for the first time I ACCEPTED as a day OFF and not just one where I lie around and feel guilty all day. It was shockingly restful. 

I’m going to keep this journey going for this year. I might not post every single day, but I will move every day, unless it’s a day off. I may not be as skinny as I used to be on my wedding day, but I’ll be happier than ever. Just typing that makes me want to cry. What a win. I’m so proud. 

THANK YOU. For the support I’ve had here this month. Quite literally that is what kept me going. I love you 💖

PS. I forgot I learned another thing. Money can buy happiness. It’s buying new clothes that fit your current body. 

 #Flowers #SelfLove

I AM BAD CINDERELLA! 🖤 and just to clear some stuff up for you, @badcinderellabway IS NOT BAD! Here’s some things I LOVED:

The cast was giving 9,000,000% at every second and is SO GOOD. The dancing (@happymeahl is slaying literally every second, kicking, slicing, lifting, the faces, I can’t.) THE MEN, literally do an entire number on SWORD PLAY where the COMMITMENT is off the charts. The ensemble is literally eating and leaving zero crumbs. @linedygenao is heartfelt and strong and simple, giving us a CONVICTED Cinderella who spoiler alert, NEEDS NO HELP- how cool is that? @thatgracemclean & @caroleecarmello OWN THAT STAGE and absolutely will have you wide eyed. The role of queen GENUINELY had me surprised at every turn. And @jordandobson_ is the sweetest price. 

Speaking of, I am OBSESSED with ‘only you, lonely you’ which is the princes song in act one. It’s got the romantics melody. And the BALL, was LUCIOUS. 

If you like Disney channel original movies, the other Cinderella’s we’ve grown up with like Brandy, big dancing and big ballgowns there is no reason you won’t have a blast at this show. It had real surprises for me in act two, like my FAVORITE THING THAT HAPPENED IN THE WHOLE SHOW I DONT WANT TO SPOIL IT FOR YOU BUT SOMETHING VERY GAY HAPPENS AND I ACTUALLY CRIED. 

I think we get wrapped up in theatre changing the world these days because we can all have opinions and we want to bash things and for them to be perfect. But 
remember, anything can be life changing for someone who is having a terrible day and needs a lift, or someone who sees themselves represented in a leading lady, or in a Gay character- the list goes on. This cast will definitely lift your spirits, and that’s enough. A genuine thank you to @badcinderellabway for that adventure in Belleville and for having me. 

PS. Glenn Close was sitting right in front of me and she very much enjoyed it.

The Trans community is under attack. Apart from what had already BEEN happening, recent developments are as follows: Mississippi & Tennessee have BANNED trans affirming care for trans minors. Oklahoma passed a bill that could ban gender affirming care for minors AND adults. Arkansas is advancing a bill that would make it ILLEGAL for a trans person to use the bathroom at the same time as a minor. And Tennessee made it Illegal to perform drag in any public places. 

Let’s start here; I’m 100% positive that the lawmakers in question have watched ‘Mrs. Doubtfire’ ‘Tootsie’ & read Shakespeare in schools & with their families. So let’s call this what it is, an attack on the LGBTQ+ community and not drag. You only care because of the connected LGBTQ+ community and performers. 

Which brings us here; there is not one single fact or piece of real scientific evidence that shows Trans (or LGBTQ+) people have harmed minors on any scale. There is also no factual evidence that Trans affirming care is unsafe, or unhelpful. There is nothing to back up the ‘protection of children’ being at stake when it comes to being around drag, or trans care. Literally there are no facts.

Which brings us here: these lawmakers and their followers are scared. They’re scared because they can visually see the world on social media and screens becoming more diverse. Becoming more accepting. And that feels like a ‘threat to the nuclear family’… however what is it really a threat to? Their control. Control of how America looks, control of guns, and the main point, control of money. 

Here’s what we need to do; be even louder that Trans is beautiful. That queer is beautiful. That being ourselves and yourself is beautiful. Lift up trans humans so they can shine brighter, and with our assistance. Be LOUDER. Because most often, a bully can’t win over a large & loud crowd. A bully can’t win an argument of opinion over facts & truths. Trans is beautiful. Shout it. 
#transisbeautiful #protecttransyouth

IF YOU EVER LISTEN TO ME ABOUT A PLAY— MAKE IT NOW. Because this play will change the world. 

THIS is what I want to see on Broadway. THIS kind of masterful story telling that surprises you and makes you laugh and is exciting to follow. THIS kind of story where the message is so strong it could change the lives of millions. THIS kind of thoughtfulness where there are trigger warnings including an announcement before the show to make the audience safe. THIS kind of collaboration where there are resources DIRECTLY and easily accessible in the program for those who have been through what the main character has been through. THIS kind of set that is meaningful and changes and even makes it RAIN? THIS kind of team, a female writer who had an important story to tell and is now telling it through a tour de force actor. THIS kind of thoughtfulness that they have PARTNERED to make sure there are entire blocks of accessible tickets for those who NEED to see this show. THIS IS THE BROADWAY I WANT. 

*TW: this play is about experiencing sexual assault* While this will sound wild to you, given this show’s subject matter,  I left feeling uplifted and like I had an amazing night at the theatre. Now it might be too much for you and take care of yourself. But the actual plot shows someone believing in a system, experiencing a system, being let down by a system, and then coming out on the other side of it with a clear message that THIS HAS TO CHANGE. It is cathartic, it is beautiful, it is hopeful, it is a masterpiece and a masterclass. 

Go see the soon to be Tony winning @jodiemcomer in this @estreetprods play by soon to be Tony winning playwright @suziemillerwriter - there is zero chance you will be disappointed. You will help change the world. Thank you for having me. Thank you for an extraordinary night.

WHY #DRESSEDFORBROADWAY? Because Broadway, and theatre in general are a very small world, and it’s hard to feel like you are a part of it. 

I spent years auditioning (even with an Equity Union Card the entire time) and getting only NOs as an actor. So I got more creative about what it meant be a part of the Broadway & Theatre community in NYC and beyond. I started to put myself in young me’s shoes. And what she lived for were glimpses of theatre life, access, accessibility, and feeling like she belonged. That’s where #DressedForBroadway and lot of what I share on here was born from. Find YES in a sea of NOs and fueling my unfulfilled creativity. 

There’s no moment in this business where you get your pass that says YOURE IN- your an actor, creative, etc forever. But you ARE apart of it. Whether you’re trying to be an actor or creative or if you’re a fan or an audience member. No theatre is possible without you. So you absolutely belong here. I hope the next show you see you’re #DressedForBroadway and know that you are keeping Theatre alive, and making it possible. I’m rooting for you. 🧡, Katie

WE ARE STILL PICKETING- and WE ARE STILL NOT BOYCOTTING!! 

I wish I could spend this week talking about one of my favorite characters but I once again believe pointing out the omission is the clearest way to send the message. We have it confirmed from SAG-AFTRA that posting about AMPTP projects even organically is crossing the picket line. 

Why is this still happening? Because these big companies are fighting against art and artists. We are at artistic war over what the future of art is. 

Companies I love are looking in to replacing my heroes with artificial intelligence, when the most magical thing in movies and television and life has always been what humans create. That original creation is not better off watered down and repurposed for something new by a machine. The human experience has always been about story telling and passing those first hand experiences down. I won’t let that go away. 

I don’t *want* to be doing this, it’s just the right thing to do. And once again there is still no call to Boycott. We are actively still seeing things, but this is my picket sign.
